Data Cloud Auto Mapping Model Card

The Auto Mapping model automatically maps data lake object (DLO) source fields to data model object (DMO) target fields. The model reduces the amount of manual labor and time required to configure new data streams in Data Cloud.

Model Details
Intended Use
Relevant Factors
Metrics
Ethical Considerations

The Auto Mapping model automatically maps DLO source fields to DMO target fields, reducing manual labor and time.
Intended use cases include platform admins mapping DLOs to the data model and solution architects implementing Data Cloud solutions.
Factors associated with the model include DLO field header names and data types, string similarity, semantic similarity, and previous mappings.

Metrics evaluate model performance, including recall, precision, and accuracy metrics aggregated and anonymized.
The model complies with relevant regulations and ensures customer privacy by encrypting data using OrgService.

Person or Organization: Salesforce Data Cloud
Model Date and Version: Pre-trained model based on MPNet
Model Type: Multi-class semantic textual similarity (STS) model

General Information: The solution is based on the sentence-transformers pretrained model “all-mpnet-base-v2”.
Licenses: Auto Mapping is available to Salesforce customers with a Data Cloud license.

Questions or Comments: Send questions or comments about the model to support@salesforce.com
